text: {| |} RFA Nasprite (A252) was a Sprite-class tanker of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary. She served during the Second World War. She was laid up in reserve at Devonport on 31 August 1954, and put up for disposal in August 1963. Category:Sprite-class tankers Category:Tankers of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary Category:1940 ships
